(Corrects spelling in headline of story published July 10.)  Dzhokhar Tsarnaev, accused of the
first deadly terrorist bombing in the U.S. since Sept. 11, 2001,
entered a courtroom for a hearing to enter a plea on charges he
killed three Boston Marathon spectators and shot a police
officer to death.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Larson in New York at 
